  "body": "I assumed it was fixed in v2.0.1 (commit 55b8ee517e06770b531807283910961d61e55d83), but I've got a fresh hardhat install from npm (v2.0.3) just today into a new project - and the retrieved Block still doesn't have mixhash parameter.\r\n\r\nI'm retrieving it by `web3.eth.getBlock(blocknumber)`\r\n\r\nWhen using the same code with Ganache - everything is okay - block has mixhash.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5636644/98843080-c23eaf80-244a-11eb-8f23-534c28929743.png)\r\n\r\nLeft is `hardhat node`, right is `ganache`",
