    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "We're doing a project involving accessing information in blocks with help of blockheader RLPs (RLP is sent to the contract by the caller).\r\nBut to verify if block header RLP and data in it is valid, and haven't been tampered - we need to hash it and get the same hash as the block hash.\r\n\r\nWithout mixHash parameter in block header - we can't form the proper RLP and hash it - thus our contracts do not work on Hardhat :-(\r\n\r\nEven if it's 0 - it's still better than \"undefined\".",
